verse.lines:
{lang-eng}This is my wonderful story,
Christ to my heart has come;
Jesus, the King of Glory,
Finds in my heart a home.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Was there e’er story so moving,
Story of love and pain;
Was there e’er Bridegroom so loving,
Seeking our hearts to gain.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}I am so glad I received Him,
Jesus my heart’s dear King;
I who so often have grieved Him,
All to His feet would bring.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}How can I ever be lonely,
How can I ever fall;
What can I want, if only
Christ is my all in all?{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Now in His bosom confiding,
This my glad song shall be;
I am in Christ abiding,
And Christ abides in me.{/lang-eng}
